Press refrigerator crescent rolls into a 15x10x1-inch baking sheet to form a crust. Bake in 350 degree F oven 12-15 minutes. Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, basil leaves and garlic powder. Spread thinly over cooled crust. Top with chopped vegetables. Sprinkle generously with Salad Supreme. Chill from 1 hour to overnight, or serve immediately.